<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00931</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR THE MODERNIZATION OF FIRE PROTECTION AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to establish a Fire Protection Service (FPS) in local government units; upgrade the existing fire protection services; establish a specialized fire protection and related services with the BFP; provide for training facilities and hiring of internationally accredited training consultants and advisers to accelerate the human resources development program; and ensure that fire protection vehicles of various types, communication equipment and facilities, and other support equipment will be equitably distributed to different fire units.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Fire Protection Modernization Act.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CABOCHAN, MANUEL III. D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Reyes (000 2019-09-13)</td><td>2. Dalipe (000 2019-09-30)</td><tr><td>3. Hernandez (000 2019-10-01)</td><td>4. Nieto (000 2019-10-02)</td><tr><td>5. Revilla (000 2019-12-18)</td><td>6. Villarica (000 2020-02-19)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ORDER AND SAFETY ON 2019-07-24</td></tr></table>